> [nekololi](#comment_476_1FzZsDQdh8wk71bDLxURPzmAt2FXehoNAB): you should know what's on your site. you should know what the .js you are serving your guests is doing to their computer, and what 3rd party fonts and css is being pulled from a centralized 3rd party cdn. no, there is no built-in protection for this. install umatrix and configure it to allow no 3rd party resources on any website by default. or use zeronet in a web browser profile specifically for zeronet, and set a proxy to 127.0.0.1 for all traffic.

how i get around this is i just have this config running on caddyserver on my personal PC, works like a charm
```
http://127.0.0.1:43110 {
   redir http://192.168.0.110{uri}
}
```
